</ul></div>
<div class="wprm-recipe wprm-recipe-snippet wprm-recipe-template-snippets-green-with-video"><a href="#recipe" data-recipe="189161" style="color: #ffffff;background-color: #5c922b;border-color: #333333;border-radius: 3px;padding: 2px 3px;" class="wprm-recipe-jump wprm-recipe-link wprm-jump-to-recipe-shortcode wprm-block-text-normal wprm-recipe-jump-inline-button wprm-recipe-link-inline-button wprm-color-accent"><span class="wprm-recipe-icon wprm-recipe-jump-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><g class="nc-icon-wrapper" fill="#ffffff"><path data-color="color-2" d="M9,2h6c0.6,0,1-0.4,1-1s-0.4-1-1-1H9C8.4,0,8,0.4,8,1S8.4,2,9,2z"></path> <path fill="#ffffff" d="M16,11V5c0-0.6-0.4-1-1-1H9C8.4,4,8,4.4,8,5v6H1.9L12,23.6L22.1,11H16z"></path></g></svg></span> Jump to Recipe</a>
</div><p>Bright colors, sweet icing, and a soft, tender bite make these cookies a joyful part of the holiday season. They look festive and cheerful on any dessert table, which makes them perfect for family gatherings, cookie trays, and homemade gifts. Their simple flavor pairs beautifully with the sweet glaze, creating a treat that feels both light and special. <img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-189026 perfmatters-lazy" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;1000&#039;%20height=&#039;667&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%201000%20667&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt width="1000" height="667" data-src="https://www.corriecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Italian-Christmas-Cookies.jpg" data-srcset="https://www.corriecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Italian-Christmas-Cookies.jpg 1000w, https://www.corriecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Italian-Christmas-Cookies-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.corriecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Italian-Christmas-Cookies-900x600.jpg 900w, https://www.corriecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Italian-Christmas-Cookies-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.corriecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Italian-Christmas-Cookies-390x260.jpg 390w" data-sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" /></p>
<p>They are fun to decorate and easy to share, which adds even more charm to the baking experience. Whether made for a celebration or just to enjoy at home, this recipe brings a lovely mix of sweetness, tradition, and holiday warmth that makes every batch feel festive and memorable.</p>
<div id="toc_container" class="no_bullets"><p class="toc_title">Table of Contents</p><ul class="toc_list"><li><a href="#Why_This_Recipe_Works">Why This Recipe Works</a></li><li><a href="#Ingredients">Ingredients</a></li><li><a href="#Tips">Tips</a></li><li><a href="#How_to_Serve">How to Serve</a></li><li><a href="#Similar_Recipes">Similar Recipes</a></li><li><a href="#Italian_Christmas_Cookies">Italian Christmas Cookies</a></li></ul></div>
<h2><span id="Why_This_Recipe_Works"><span style="color: #ff6600;"><strong>Why This Recipe Works</strong></span></span></h2>
<p>This recipe works because it uses basic ingredients that create a soft and tender cookie. Butter adds richness, while eggs help hold everything together. Baking powder gives the cookies a light texture without making them dry. The simple glaze adds sweetness and keeps the cookies moist.</p>
<p>Another reason to make this recipe is how reliable and flexible it is. The dough is easy to shape, and the cookies bake evenly. You can change the flavor by using almond or vanilla extract, and decorate them with different sprinkles. They stay soft for days, making them perfect for preparing ahead during busy holiday celebrations.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-189024 perfmatters-lazy" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;1000&#039;%20height=&#039;667&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%201000%20667&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt width="1000" height="667" data-src="https://www.corriecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Italian-Christmas-Cookies-2.jpg" data-srcset="https://www.corriecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Italian-Christmas-Cookies-2.jpg 1000w, https://www.corriecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Italian-Christmas-Cookies-2-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.corriecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Italian-Christmas-Cookies-2-900x600.jpg 900w, https://www.corriecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Italian-Christmas-Cookies-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.corriecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Italian-Christmas-Cookies-2-390x260.jpg 390w" data-sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" /></p>
<h2><span id="Ingredients"><span style="color: #ff6600;"><strong>Ingredients</strong></span></span></h2>
<p><strong>Flour: </strong>Flour gives the cookies their soft structure.<br />
Substitute: All-purpose gluten-free flour blend.</p>
<p><strong>Sugar: </strong>Sugar sweetens the cookies and helps them brown lightly.<br />
Substitute: Fine white sugar.</p>
<p><strong>Butter: </strong>Butter makes the cookies soft and rich.<br />
Substitute: Unsalted margarine.</p>
<p><strong>Eggs: </strong>Eggs help bind the dough and keep cookies tender.<br />
Substitute: No perfect substitute for traditional texture.</p><div class='code-block code-block-4' style='margin: 8px 0; clear: both;'>
<input type="hidden" name="IL_IN_ARTICLE"></div>

<p><strong>Almond extract: </strong>Almond extract gives the cookies their classic Italian flavor.<br />
Substitute: Vanilla extract.</p>
<h2><span id="Tips"><span style="color: #ff6600;"><strong>Tips</strong></span></span></h2>
<ul>
<li>Do not overmix the dough.</li>
<li>Chill dough if it feels sticky.</li>
<li>Bake until lightly golden, not dark.</li>
<li>Let cookies cool before glazing.</li>
<li>Add sprinkles while glaze is still wet.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-189025 perfmatters-lazy" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;1000&#039;%20height=&#039;667&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%201000%20667&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt width="1000" height="667" data-src="https://www.corriecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Italian-Christmas-Cookies-3.jpg" data-srcset="https://www.corriecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Italian-Christmas-Cookies-3.jpg 1000w, https://www.corriecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Italian-Christmas-Cookies-3-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.corriecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Italian-Christmas-Cookies-3-900x600.jpg 900w, https://www.corriecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Italian-Christmas-Cookies-3-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.corriecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Italian-Christmas-Cookies-3-390x260.jpg 390w" data-sizes="auto, (max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" /></p>
<h2><span id="How_to_Serve"><span style="color: #ff6600;"><strong>How to Serve</strong></span></span></h2>
<p>Italian Christmas cookies are best served at room temperature. They are soft and lightly sweet with a simple glaze on top.</p>
<ul>
<li>Serve them on a holiday cookie tray.</li>
<li>Pair them with coffee or tea.</li>
<li>Package them in gift boxes for festive sharing.</li>
</ul>
<h2><span id="Similar_Recipes"><span style="color: #ff6600;">Similar Recipes</span></span></h2>
<p><a href="https://www.corriecooks.com/lemon-puff-cookies/">Lemon Puff Cookies</a></p>
<p><a href="https://www.corriecooks.com/chocolate-crinkle-cookies/">Chocolate Crinkle Cookies</a></p>
<p><a href="https://www.corriecooks.com/butterscotch-cookies/">Butterscotch Cookies</a></p>
